race.comment: Tricky contest with plenty of form angles. SEA ADMIRAL (3) produced a good set of figures when winning first-up at Nowra. Then covered ground in the run when a sound fifth over 1000m at Gosford in BM64 grade. Find a weaker race from the good gate and Latham sticks. LET'S GO BRANDON (7) capable on his day and has a decent win in him this campaign. Showed a ton of courage first-up with the 58kg when fourth over 1000m at Wagga. Nose roll goes on and has the speed to get across from the gate. IOWNA BENZ (5) resumes with a handy fresh record. Sat on the speed with the 60kg when a fading last over 1100m here last October. Back without a trial and the claim will help her cause. STORMFIELD (8) blinkers come off for this after he went out hard and knocked up in the straight to finish fourth over 1200m at Gosford. Won here two back and has the speed to get across from the wide gate. Stays win the mix.
